Home Home Meet the Team Vortexed Innovation Council Vortex Man Contact Home Meet the Team Vortexed Innovation Council Vortex Man Contact Who we are Vortexed was created in response to the whirlwind of excitement around Vortex Man and his universe of environment friendly characters and Vortexed is an inclusive, diverse, and accessible modern community that is committed to equality, social and environmental Saving the Earth includes all cultures and anyone who wants to make a positive impact on the Through entertaining and bringing awareness to the real environmental issues taking place in the world today called for the Vortexed founders to create an ecosystem of technology that helps manufacturers, retailers, and generations of consumers connect to make a positive impact on our Vortexed makes for an interactive and fun community and incentivizes these groups to make a difference by attaching value to product packaging that enable the circularity of our economy by engaging the consumer beyond the Our Mission ​ Our mission is to save our Earth by uniting partners and consumers to drive change in how we perceive Our goal is to engage families and future generations to make necessary changes to enable the circular economy through educating and incentivizing the consumer with rewards for making responsible choices with product Everything has value in our and it is up to ​us as a society to drive that positive change for future ​​ ​ Copyright © Vortexed   Contact - Incite Strategies, LLC Main Suite Vancouver, WA (503) © Incite All rights Every situation is We work with each of our clients so that we can tailor solutions that work best for What are you struggling with? Living with damaged credit makes you feel stuck in the same vicious cycle of high interest rates, debt that never seems to get paid down and seemingly unachievable financial No matter what your situation may be - whether you are trying to buy a home or achieve financial freedom - Incite Strategies will tear down the barriers so nothing holds back your credit and financial success ! It’s time to break the negative credit Client login | How it works Resources FAQ SCHEDULE A FREE CREDIT CONSULTATION GET STARTED Hi, I m Ivory! Calculated from your trade These are realized gains from stock and options trades and include deductions for commissions Commissions This is a roll up of all commissions you ve paid on all trade confirmations added to the Average Commission This is equal to the total commissions paid divided by the number of trades Trade Board Data When you upload a CSV, your trade confirmations are rolled up into your Trade Board, which is an aggregation of trade data by Symbol This is the stock symbol for the underlying Quantity This is the quantity of shares that you currently have in your Cost Basis The cost basis for the quantity of shares in your portfolio is an average of all of the purchases of When you sell shares, the quantity is reduced by the amount sold at the average When you buy more shares, the quantity purchased is added to the quantity and a new average price is Adjusted Cost Basis This is your cost basis from above adjusted with options income and commission You can use this number to know, for example, if you sell covered calls at a particular price, whether or not that would put you at an overall loss if the stock were to be called Let s say you bought shares at $20 and sold a Call option for $0.50 and paid $1.00 in Then your adjusted cost basis for those shares is $2,000 - $50 + $1.00 all divided by = $19.51 Proceeds These are the cumulative proceeds received or paid for both stock and option Capital Gains Same as the summary capital gains, this is the total capital gains for the particular symbol inclusive of options trades and commission Commissions Total Emprendimiento: 7 pasos para crear tu propio negocio - Flexinumber Saltar al contenido Flexinumber Servicios Flexi Básico Flexi Profesional Flexi Empresa WSP Multiagente Planes Nosotros Blog Contacto Menú Servicios Flexi Básico Flexi Profesional Flexi Empresa WSP Multiagente Planes Nosotros Blog Contacto Instagram Categorías Blog Emprendimiento: 7 pasos para crear tu propio negocio Si has decidido ser un emprendedor, toma en cuenta estas recomendaciones para crear y hacer despegar tu Los negocios digitales están a la orden del Autor de la entrada Por franklin Fecha de la entrada de octubre de Ser un emprendedor es un desafío en cualquier parte del mundo, ya que supone un arduo trabajo para sacar adelante un proyecto que implica tiempo, esfuerzo e De hecho, cerca del % de los emprendimientos fracasan en el primero año de vida , periodo conocido como la curva de la muerte . Latinoamérica es una región en el que los emprendimientos se mantienen en franco Por ejemplo, en Chile, solo en marzo de este año los servicios digitales para el comercio electrónico crecieron en hasta % , de acuerdo con datos del Banco Interamericano de Desarrollo (BID). En México, hasta mediados del , y pese a la pandemia, los inversionistas ya habían realizado acuerdos para otorgar recursos a las de base tecnológica por un valor de millones de dólares . Mientras que en Perú el número de emprendimientos ha crecido de manera sostenida durante la pandemia . Así, la cifra ha subido de ,9% en julio a ,9% en octubre, de acuerdo con una encuesta online realizada por la empresa de investigación Activa El contexto ha obligado que los nuevos negocios sean Como ves, cada vez más personas optan por ser Por ello, te dejamos unos consejos para montar tu propia empresa . ¿Cómo iniciar tu propio negocio desde cero? Identifica una necesidad El centro debe ser el cliente , por lo que entender sus requerimientos y hallar soluciones acordes a las mismas es No debes cometer el error de pensar que tu propuesta, por más buena que sea, se aplica a todos los Primero, consulta y recoge Investiga Después de hallada la necesidad, a verigua todo lo referente a tu producto o servicio y el mercado en el que se mueve . Identifica a tus competidores, cuáles son sus precios, dónde están ubicados y qué es aquello que comparten Para el caso de los clientes, realiza una segmentación y encuentra lo que les motivaría a Realiza un proceso creativo Es momento de crear el nombre del emprendimiento, establecer una ubicación para comenzar a operar (puede ser presencial o remota), escoger a las personas que llevarán a cabo el proyecto y saber qué recursos También, determina la fecha de inicio de tu Desarrolla la propuesta de negocio Identifica fortalezas, debilidades, oportunidades y amenazas para ajustar diversos aspectos de la En este punto podrás analizar costos fijos y variables, inversión, proveedores, distribución, precio y actividades esenciales para entregar una propuesta de Forma un equipo de trabajo Nuestra cultura nos empuja a querer hacer todo de manera personal . Si bien ello no es malo, necesitarás personas de Por ejemplo, si quieres lanzar un negocio nuevo de comida, requerirás sumar elementos para las ventas, el marketing, la distribución, Debes aprender a confiar en tu equipo para tener éxito en el Implementa un modelo de negocio Da inicio a la venta del producto o servicio diseñado, considerando procesos contables y financieros, con el fin de ir midiendo los resultados Es importante saber cuándo comenzará tu negocio a ser rentable (punto de equilibrio) y en qué momento recuperarás la inversión Trabaja en el crecimiento Una vez lograda la recuperación de la inversión, la obtención de una estructura definida y rentable y un incremento sostenido en el tiempo de las ventas, entonces estarás en el momento de Puede ser la integración de nuevos productos o servicios, o la apertura de una sucursal o nuevos puntos de venta, así como también ingresar a mercados extranjeros que te permitan expandir tu negocio a nuevos clientes o nuevos En esta coyuntura, los negocios tienden a digitalizarse, y son los consumidores quienes reclaman nuevas Por ejemplo, en Perú existen más de 6 millones de compradores en línea que pueden solicitar delivery . Flexinumber es tu mejor opción para tu Podrás contar con WhatsApp Business y WhatsApp personal en el mismo equipo para facilitar tus ventas y hacer crecer tu Conoce más de este servicio aquí . ¿Quieres chatear con nosotros? ingresa a este enlace . RUDD REPORT May, Public health experts emphasize the need for regulations limiting unhealthy food marketing to children to help solve the childhood obesity crisis however, increased public support is necessary to implement such We conducted six focus groups with Caucasian, Hispanic and African American parents in which we explored potential ways to increase awareness of the harmful effects of food marketing in order to enhance support for government policies limiting these In general, parents expressed low awareness of food marketing and its negative impact on Yet examples of current food marketing practices presented during the groups effectively convinced many parents that the issue merits further Some parents supported solutions and wanted to personally engage in actions to address the Despite their support, many parents also perceived potential barriers to the effective implementation of proposed This qualitative research demonstrates that increased awareness of food marketing practices targeting children together with examples of potential actions that can be enacted at the local level are likely to increase support for solutions to address the These findings suggest a significant opportunity for communities and advocacy groups to educate parents and effectively enlist their support for local action to limit food marketing to IN A FOREIGN LAND - Personal information we collect When you visit the Site, we automatically collect certain information about your device, including information about your web browser, IP address, time zone, and some of the cookies that are installed on your Additionally, as you browse the Site, we collect information about the individual web pages or products that you view, what websites or search terms referred you to the Site, and information about how you interact with the We refer to this information as “Device Information”. We collect Device Information using the following technologies: “Cookies” are data files that are placed on your device or computer and often include an anonymous unique (For more information about cookies, and how to disable cookies, visit http: www.allaboutcookies.org.) “Log files” track actions occurring on the Site, and collect data including your IP address, browser type, Internet service provider, referring exit pages, and date time “Web beacons”, “tags”, and “pixels” are electronic files used to record information about how you browse the Additionally when you make a purchase or attempt to make a purchase through the Site, we collect certain information from you, including your name, billing address, shipping address, payment information (including credit card numbers), email address, and phone We refer to this information as “Order Information”. When we talk about “Personal Information” in this Privacy Policy, we are talking both about Device Information and Order How do we use your personal information? We use the Order Information that we collect generally to fulfill any orders placed through the Site (including processing your payment information, arranging for delivery, and providing you with invoices and or order confirmations). Additionally, we use this Order Information to: Communicate with you Screen our orders for potential risk or fraud and When in line with the preferences you have shared with us, provide you with information or advertising relating to our products or We use the Device Information that we collect to help us screen for potential risk and fraud (in particular, your IP address), and more generally to improve and optimize our Site (for example, by generating analytics about how our customers browse and interact with the Site, and to assess the success of our marketing and advertising campaigns). Sharing you personal Information We share your Personal Information with third parties to help us use your Personal Information, as described For example, we use facebook to collect data for our store and learn about the people in contact with our We also use Google Analytics to help us understand how our customers use the Site -- you can read more about how Google uses your Personal Information here: https: www.google.com intl en policies privacy . Employees Occupational Illness Compensation Program Act (EEOICPA) was created to help provide medical benefits and financial compensation to workers exposed to radiation during the age of nuclear weapons For accepted illnesses, this program may compensate up to $400,000 as well as cover % of medical expenses related to your awarded Part B of the EEOICPA Part B provides benefits to eligible current or former employees of the DOE, and certain of its vendors, contractors and subcontractors, and to certain survivors of such individuals as provided in the To be eligible, an employee must have sustained a radiogenic cancer, chronic silicosis, beryllium sensitivity, or chronic beryllium disease while in the performance of duty at a covered DOE facility, atomic weapons employer facility or a beryllium vendor facility during a specified period of With Part B, provides benefits in the amount of $150,000 and covers medical expenses related to the accepted Also with Part B, provides for payment of a smaller of $50,000 to individuals (who also receive medical benefits) or their eligible survivors, who were determined to be eligible for compensation under section 5 of Part B: SEC Part E of the EEOICPA Part E provides benefits to DOE contractor and subcontractor employees and to certain uranium workers who developed a covered illness as a result of exposure to any toxic substance (including the three covered by Part B) at a DOE facility or RECA section 5 facility, as It grants covered employees a federal payment based on the level of impairment and or years of qualifying if they developed a covered illness as a result of exposure to toxic Certain survivors of deceased workers are also eligible to receive compensation, if the covered illness caused, aggravated or contributed to the employee’s Additionally, Part E provides that a maximum aggregate compensation of $250,000 can be paid to all claimants as a result of the exposure of a covered Part E Employee and also covers medical expenses related to covered Part E The EEOICPA Medical Benefits Card Do you have this white card? Overview - DC Link - Advanced Conversion Skip to content Powerful Capacitor Solutions for Demanding Applications Contact Us for Info & Product Orders 1 (802) Powerful Capacitor Solutions for Demanding Applications Home About Products Technology DC Link Overview Traction Drive Aviation Grid Tied Systems Alternative Energy DC Link Overview Pulsed Power Overview AC Filter & Resonator Overview Technology Overview Technical Papers Contact - Overview test caption The DC link is a critical component for inverters utilizing fast switching that is often overlooked during the initial stages of The capacitor draws a continuous current from the DC source while supplying the charge needed for the fast switching events and effectively functions as a charge Traditionally, the DC link capacitor has been treated as an afterthought of the design with a crude bus structure implemented to connect with conventional commodity capacitor However, efficient fast switching using advanced silicon and wide bandgap devices requires a carefully designed DC link bus topology with tightly integrated The Advanced Conversion annular form factor film capacitor is ideally suited for “surface mounting” to an optimized bus structure that interfaces with the switch This patented approach combined with bus cooling provides a very high Ampere per rating to allow the smallest possible capacitance while simultaneously minimizing the commutation loop As such, the per is defined by inverter control limitations rather than by capacitor life and the DC bus can be safely operated at a higher voltage due to reduced overshoot during Equivalent series inductance values of less than are readily achieved using the right switch module with an appropriate connection Please download our DC Link Technology Overview presentation (pdf link) for more Optimized Bus Structures Advanced Conversion specializes in complete solutions including the design and fabrication of the bus We made the decision to bring this capability in house to provide faster lead times along with advanced design and fabrication capabilities for custom Our unique patented and proprietary technology for mounting annular form factor windings to terminals and bus layers eliminates thermal expansion mismatch problems and eliminates the weight and cost of redundant copper that occurs when conventional discrete capacitors are mounted on a The surface mounting approach also eliminates connections, maintaining high current capability, and preserves the surface of the bus opposite the capacitor for other components or direct interfacing with a cooling We support a variety of electric vehicles, aerospace, alternative energy, and applications with this novel Note that Advanced Conversion also offers a suite of optimized discrete capacitors and standard capacitor bus “test kits” designed around popular switch module Working with our customers Advanced Conversion best serves our customers by engaging early in the design process, working to understand the application, and mutually agreeing upon a practical The capacitor winding can be considered analogous to the die in a device as the basic functional element which must then be properly packaged and One or more windings are specified to meet the capacitance need subject volumetric requirements and the mission profile of the DC link voltage and ripple current, exactly the same as paralleled die are specified in a switch However, the capacitor element(s) must be fully integrated with proper electrical and thermal coupling to the customer system to achieve the best Ultimately, the capacitor bus structure of the DC link defines the backbone of the inverter topology and has a significant impact on both the commutation inductance and thermal Lastly, the capacitance solution is the single largest influencer on volume for the end Advanced Conversion provides a high level of application engineering support for our customers using the following process: Provide a shopping list of parameters for the customer to fill out (pdf) Sanity check of capacitor size given complete mission profile Budgetary quotation for design and custom prototype build % down payment required to commit engineering resources for custom projects Detailed review and finalization of the customer specification Thermal and electrical analysis if required Demonstrate required life given mission profile Work full mechanical design details with customer and submit final CAD for approval Final quotation for prototype build Prototype build Our team, once committed, can usually work as fast or faster than the customer can interact with the design Typical design projects take from 4 – weeks but that is usually Prototypes can be built in 8 – weeks for many This is faster than just the bus bars themselves from typical industry We welcome your application Please contact us at this email to get the process Test kits A properly designed DC link is essential to properly evaluate switch module Advanced Conversion

Today, economic growth is primarily contingent on increased resource In this linear economic approach, organizations harvest or extract materials, use them to create products, and then sell those products to consumers who generally incinerate or send to landfill the materials that no longer serve their original As the population grows and the negative environmental impact of resource extraction continues, this “take, make, waste” model is quickly reaching its The circular economy, by contrast, is one that is “restorative and regenerative by design, and aims to keep products, components, and materials at their highest utility and value at all times” (Ellen MacArthur Foundation, ). Here are some pioneers leading the way to a circular According to a report by McKinsey in collaboration with the World Economic Forum and the Ellen MacArthur Foundation, US$1 trillion a year could be generated by for the global The market momentum is clearly accelerating with major corporations committing toward circular A survey conducted by ING in interviewing executives found that % of American companies now plan to move toward Nearly twice as many companies say that they are embedding sustainability in strategic in compared to How will enable businesses to move towards a Circular Economy? consumer goods currently account for per cent of material inputs into the economy and per cent of municipal waste according to McKinsey paper “Towards the Circular Economy”. Therefore, an important use case is that of packaging of consumable Specifically, the reuse of packaging will deliver dramatically greater materials savings and profit than the traditional linear A retailer in South America is leading the way to create a circular retail business for common household goods using reusable plastic bottle The company created fixed and mobile refill stations using vending machines at convenient locations for consumers to the products by reusing the plastic In doing so, consumers are rewarded with loyalty points that can be used against future For this business model to run smoothly data needs to be easily exchanged among the involved parties since each of the fixed and mobile refill stations is equipped with various sensors, such as temperature, humidity, fill Also, the vending machines each have their own set of The sensors and devices provide data to the retailer that enables data driven For example, the fill level sensor shows the retailer when to replenish the vending machine or which locations are performing better than Furthermore, the retailer would want to perform analytics on the data to understand consumer purchasing Suppliers would also need the data to understand what products are selling well vs To make the whole business model function seamlessly, the retailer needs to establish a data infrastructure for the relevant data to be present at various stages of the business provides a secure, trusted data exchange infrastructure to enable the entire business cycle, from manufacturers to retailers to IoT sensors and devices securely capture and protect the data at the source, which we called the Edge . A ’ Edge Data Guardian is installed at each refill station acting as a data collector to aggregate all the relevant It then processes the data to support the company’s operational The data is then encrypted before forwarding to the company’s central data center for analytics and other A ’ Edge Data Port at the data center securely anonymize the incoming data and packages them for external party Suppliers and other business partners can obtain access keys from ’ Edge Data Bridge to access the anonymized data stored in the retailer’s Edge Data The diagram below illustrates the high level architecture of the solution: Click here for more ​ CLIMATE CHANGE What is Climate Change? ModelFront - Evaluation ModelFront Solutions Plans Docs About Console Evaluation Automated evaluation for machine translation researchers and developers Still chasing BLEU, waiting for human evals and fighting fires? Neural machine translation has changed the But the problems of life as a machine translation researcher have not changed: BLEU obsession, slow human evals and random catastrophic translation Those problems are not Google, Microsoft and everybody else know that BLEU isn t useful when it comes to very good translations or very bad But what is the alternative? Find your fails before your users do ModelFront finds translation Now we re offering to help machine translation teams Leveraging our risk prediction technology, we catch your translation fails, scalably and Fail lists With big lists of fails, you can understand and fix problems in your dataset, pipeline or approach, and also apply patches before there s Fail rates With the rates of fails per million, you can compare systems and versions, and protect against nasty regressions in the long Fail reports We summarize our findings, and report to you possible major or minor bugs in your pipeline or Useful metrics ModelFront lists and rates include a breakdown by error Structure Errors with words dropped or inserted, and errors with agreement Untranslated Errors with words left untranslated, or translated to the wrong language Names Errors with literally translated or mixed up person names, placenames, brand names, product names, and org names Symbols Errors with numbers, prices, dates, codes, URLs, emails, hashtags and usernames Locale Errors around localisation of numbers, prices, dates and quotes Formatting Errors with casing and punctuation Semantics Errors with negation, context, function words, content words, ambiguity, and idioms Robustness Robustness to input that is wrong language, very long, mixed language, wrong script, missing diacritics, bad encoding, character variants, spelling variants, typos, missing spaces, casing, punctuation, and out of distribution Scandals Translations that are NSFW, offensive or violent, or mix up named entities Fast and continuous ModelFront quality evaluations are scalable and You can compare systems, perform grid search, set up continuous integrations or monitoring on fresh incoming How is it different than quality evaluation, like BLEU? BLEU requires a reference translation, and doesn t distinguish between stylistic variations and scandalous translation Today there are systems that have roughly the same BLEU score as human translators, but translation fails still ModelFront requires no reference translation, doesn t get triggered by output that is noisy or machiny but good enough, and also covers the long How is it different than quality estimation (QE)? The main metric in the QE task is Like BLEU, it focuses on edit distance or time, so it does not distinguish stylistic variations from scandalous translation Unlike BLEU, it doesn t require reference translations, but it does require labelled training QE is most useful in that context of CAT platforms for human ModelFront is built specifically to catch really bad How is it different than translation? If only it were that easy! translations often match the original even when the translation was This could be because of identity translations - words or phrases that failed to translate - or literal translations - of an idiom or semantically ambigous word or phrase - or just bad training data that causes corresponding errors in both On the other hand, translations often don t match the original even when the translation was Every language has distinctions that it cannot represent, both structural - for example, between cases, tenses, formality or genders - or semantic - because of homonyms, including named entities, and So a translation is too often a lossy represention of the For the many indirect pairs , there is additional ModelFront uses translations, but it s a small signal among How is it different than confidence? Modern neural models have some clue about their own confidence, but many if not most translation fails are due to bad data or the inherent complexity of human Glassbox techniques can fail precisely when translation On the other hand, confidence may be low just because there are multiple synonymous ModelFront is an independent system, specifically focused on risk Translation engines are blackboxes to How is it different than hardcoding approaches? approaches can be very effective for certain error types, number formats, or in certain scenarios, when there is an extensive translation Notable examples include LexiQA, WMT test suites, or features offered within CAT tools like Smartling and ModelFront predictions come from deep learning models, including unlabelled data, to scale robustly on unseen data, variations, and noise, across language Is it automated, or just crowdsourcing? ModelFront predictions come from deep learning models, not crowds

FAQs | Lenderfit | United States Features Pricing Demo FAQs Blog Login FAQs GETTING STARTED How long does it take to integrate Lenderfit into our process? Upon signing a master service agreement (MSA), we will arrange a series of remote meetings with the goal of having you fully operational within 2 weeks! Do I need to download any software? Nope, we take care of Simply and you can start creating your first loan product! Is there any engineering involved with onboarding? We didn t like the idea of a 6 month onboarding period, largely due to custom Instead, you re in control when it comes to Want to add a new loan product? No problem! You can get started We look forward to continual improvement and rolling out new features for all of our customers SECURITY Securing Data at Rest Lenderfit stores data at rest using , storage This is the level of protection that banks use to keep your account information ​ Securing Data in Transit Lenderfit uses Transport Level Security (TLS) with SSL for all data requests and This ensures network communications are secure for information to be transferred into or out of our ​ Cloud Data Centers Lenderfit’s cloud data centers are SSAE18 SOC 2 Type II certified meaning their facilities have multiple layers of access controls including onsite security In addition their Information Security Management Systems have been ISO 27018 certified ensuring high standards for information security processes and industry best ​ Loan Application Monitoring Lenderfit uses the Activity Log on each loan application to track events and communication between the loan officer and the The Activity Log is visible by both parties and help to ensure accurate records and ​ Authentication Lenderfit requires strong password standards to be enabled to further protect against unauthorized ​ Two Factor Authentication Two Factor Authentication is available for both lenders and their ​ LENDERFIT How does Lenderfit work? We strive for the most intuitive software Within Lenderfit, individual users can create new loan product templates, integrate their own materials, invite applicants to provide information and track small details that are critical to understanding how decisions are made ​ Can I use Lenderfit for Technical Assistance? Yes! We encourage you to start offering technical assistance through Please request a demo to learn Can I utilize my templates, applications and other materials on Lenderfit? Yes! You can attach links to existing tools and upload documents to checklist items in Is Lenderfit Team Friendly? Yes, other members of your team can easily view projects and assist in moving an applicant forward while coworkers are out sick or on Internal notes allow Lenders to make comments during the application process that are only visible to members of your What is a Loan Product? A product in Lenderfit is represented by a template checklist that can be with examples, templates and Our framework for managing applications makes it as easy as possible for applicants to provide information in an expedited Anyone in an organization can create a template Loan Product for that organization to use when inviting applicants into the document collection What is a Checklist? All of the items you ll need from a client to make a final Lenderfit checklists are in the cloud, meaning the Lender and the applicant are working on the same checklist at the same Essential checklist items are fully customizable allowing you to collect whatever is Milestones are fully customizable as What is a Milestone? Milestones allow Lenders to create more transparency during the application Applicants can only work on items up to a set Milestone, however, they can still see what will be required moving forward with the lending Milestones allow you to collect information in phases, and various internal review They can also be used to identify any required technical assistance or completion of training Who can use Lenderfit? Lenders, technical assistance providers and their How many users can use Lenderfit? The delta between our individual pricing and small team pricing is very We want to make it as easy as possible for small teams to afford multiple user If you’ll need more than 4 user accounts, please email to discuss our enterprise Can I pull credit through Lenderfit? We do not currently support the ability to pull You can certainly upload a copy of a report pulled by you from a third party to complete a checklist item in Lenderfit for loan package You are also able to ask for a copy of a credit report from an applicant as a checklist Can I sign documents through Lenderfit? We do not currently support electronic Attaching fully executed docs is a great way to wrap up the application Clients will have quick access to those documents into the future should they need another ​ BILLING What forms of payment do you accept ? This isn’t the only suggestion or exercise used by companies to correct harmful silo However other suggestions and exercises are usually too general or Writing, reviewing and refining documents is the missing step for Here’s how this communication and workflow method takes silo mentality corrections from general to The Communication and Silo Mentality Connection A silo mentality generally refers to different departments or groups failing to work together This results in rework, missed deadlines, faulty handoffs, unforced errors and a wide range of communication Here are some examples: Two teams work on nearly identical projects for weeks or months without informing each A design graphic asset must be because a legal review is done after the Various teams or individuals provide contradicting copy Two managers have entirely different processes for reviewing work and providing Two new employees in different departments receive conflicting information about processes and And so In most silo cases, multiple departments are It’s not driven but any team or person, and goes beyond trivial communication Writing, reading and refining documents as a team improves workplace confidence while addressing The three components of this include document reviews, document requests and the implementation of the discussed Document reviews clue teams into ongoing or upcoming It increases the amount of time for deep focus and Heavy research and clear writing expose potential problems before any work Providing Silo Solutions The internet is with suggestions on how to break down Much of the advice is relevant and smart but lacks specific or practical Here’s how this style of communication naturally implements these common suggestions: Suggestion 1: Encourage and incentivize collaboration This suggestion is general but there’s support behind The IKEA effect has been documented by psychologists (pre-IKEA). People who put effort into something before or as it’s being created are inherently more Creating a culture of writing, reading and refining memos means different voices and contributions are brought to the Tableau CEO Adam Selipsky relies on document reviews (narrative) for his company and said , “There’s a lot more democratic participation in the discussion by using the " This input gives team members the incentive to collaborate with each other by writing and providing feedback on It provides a feeling of ownership, just like when you finish building the Dagstorp from Suggestion 2: Tea

As described, the main benefit of life insurance is that it offers a way to provide financially for your family members if something unexpected should That can include: Replacing your salary income for years to come Leaving a significant inheritance for future generations Covering funeral costs, which are often more expensive than people realize Paying for federate and state death estate taxes Proving an opportunity for charitable donations get your free quote Find Insurance What Are the Different Types of Life Insurance? There are two primary types of life insurance you can purchase: Term Life and Whole Letâs dig a little deeper into Term Life insurance Term Life insurance is simple in that it only pays benefits if the person insured dies during the terms of the (And it should be noted that policies can range anywhere from one to thirty ) So, if you were to pass away during the time range for the policy, your beneficiaries would receive the financial There is one more wrinkle for Most policies keep the same death benefit (the amount of money paid out after your death) throughout the entire However, some policies, called âdecreasing termâ policies, lower the death benefit for each year of the policy Thatâs a way to potentially save some money on the premiums, but it also potentially reduces the benefit your family would Whole Life insurance Whole Life insurance is different from Term Life insurance in two main First, whole life policies usually last for the entirety of your (They last for your âwhole life,â in other ) And you typically pay the same premium for as long as you have the Second, Whole Life policies have cash Meaning, you can actually benefit from the policy without You can withdraw some or all of the cash value, and even use it as collateral to borrow Forbes wrote an interesting article about it being considered an Find Insurance get your free quote How Much Does Life Insurance Cost? Thereâs no set amount for a Rather, the cost is based on several factors that are specific to you as an However, there are some principles that are generally true when it comes to pricing life insurance: The higher the benefit, the higher the The younger you are as a policy holder, the lower the The healthier you are as a policy holder, the lower the (And the opposite is true: if you have dealt with significant health challenges in the past, you will likely find high ) Term Life is generally less expensive than Whole Find Insurance get your free quote How Much Life Insurance Do You Need? Once again, the amount of life insurance that makes sense for your situation is However, there are some key questions you can ask when determining how much insurance you need: How much can you afford to pay each month for premiums? How many dependents are currently reliant on your income as their sole source of security? What are the immediate expenses that would need to be covered if you were to pass away? (Including debts, funeral costs, taxes, and so ) What are the expenses that your family will need to cover without your income? (Including college, down payments on homes, weddings, and so ) Are there charitable organizations you would like to receive donations after your death? get your free quote 5 Life Insurance Mistakes You Can Avoid Be prepared so you can make good decisions and choose the right coverage for Life insurance is a great investment for most people and most But there are still lots of opportunities to

Seamly - Cross Platform Business Messaging Start for Free! Seamly Documentation Agent App Features Support Request Queueing: Queues collect all incoming requests into a single channel for your support agents to easily ‘PickUp’. Private Conversations: Individual private channels keep conversation history neat and tidy no matter how they choose to contact Usage Creating queue channels Use the ‘Create new Queue’ button or the seamly create command to create a new queue channel that you can then add agents and clients Adding Agents to a Queue To add a new support agent to a queue channel (which allows them to view and respond to incoming support requests), use the seamly addagent command within the queue NOTE: This is the only way to add an agent to a queue If you try to use the built in Slack invite command the action will be immediately reverted and you’ll receive a notification saying to use the Seamly Adding Clients to a Queue There are few ways to invite clients or client teams to join a queue Inviting a Slack Team To send an invite to another Slack team, use one of the following methods: Click the ‘Invite a Client’ button from the Seamly app home message or Use the seamly addclient command within the queue Once you fill out the information in the dialog box and submit it, an email invite will be sent to the client for them to Sending SMS only invites to client phones If you have clients that don’t use Slack and just want to be able to text your business phone number for support, you can send them and SMS only To do this, go to your dashboard at https: business.seamly.chat , select your agent team, then click ‘Add a Client Team’ at the Add the individual clients names and phone numbers for the team and they’ll receive a text with a contact card and a welcome Removing Agents from Queue To remove an agent from a queue they are currently part of, use the seamly kickagent NOTE: This is the only way to remove an agent from a queue If you try to use the built in Slack kick command the action will be immediately reverted and you’ll receive a notification saying to use the Seamly Picking Up Conversations When a support request comes in, it’ll be directed to the queue channel for that Agents that are part of that queue can click the ‘Pickup’ button at the bottom of the message, or the seamly pickup command to PickUp the first client in the queue of waiting Closing Conversations After an agent has dealt with a support request within the private conversation with a client, they can close out the conversation by using the seamly close command within the client’s personal private ‍ Client App The Seamly Client app has very limited functionality and simply exists to facilitate direct communication between you and the support team for the company that’s providing you When you receive an email invite from another Slack team, you will simply install the client app and accept the invite using the ‘Accept Invite’ button from the app home message Once that’s completed a private channel will be created for you and any other user within your team who has authorized the From there you will use that channel to contact that support Privacy Terms of Service Documentation That’s just so we can personalize your new account and identify messages coming from you into the We’ll never sell your personal info to third parties, and we won’t use your name or company in marketing statements without your permission, When you pay for Seamly, we ask for your credit card and billing That’s so we can charge you for service, calculate taxes due, and send you Your credit card is passed directly to our payment processor and doesn’t ever go through our We store a record of the payment transaction, including the last 4 digits of the credit card number, for account history, invoicing, and billing We store your billing address to calculate any sales tax due in the United States, to detect fraudulent credit card transactions, and to print on your When you write Seamly with a question or to ask for help, we’ll keep that correspondence, and the email address, for future When you browse our marketing pages, we’ll track that for statistical purposes (like conversion rates and to test new designs).
